# Privacy Policy

Effective date: 23.06.2026

This Privacy Policy explains how **What to Watch** handles information.

**What to Watch** is operated by **Positive Lab**.

## 1. Overview

What to Watch is a video discovery app that helps users browse short clips and decide what to watch next.

The app is designed to be simple and privacy-friendly. It does not require users to create an account or log in.

## 2. Information We Do Not Collect

What to Watch does not collect:

* Name
* Email address
* Phone number
* Precise location
* Contacts
* Photos or videos from your device
* Camera or microphone data
* Payment information

The app does not require account registration or login.

## 3. Analytics and Advertising

What to Watch does not use third-party analytics tools.

What to Watch does not show ads.

What to Watch does not use advertising networks or tracking SDKs.

## 4. Information Stored on Your Device

If you save clips in the app, this saved status may be stored locally on your device.

This helps the app remember which clips you saved.

This information is not used to identify you personally.

You can remove this data by clearing the app data or uninstalling the app.

## 5. Technical Server Data

When the app loads video content or connects to our backend, our servers may automatically process basic technical information needed to operate the app, such as:

* IP address
* Device or app request information
* Date and time of request
* Requested video files or API endpoints
* Error logs

This information is used only to operate, secure, debug, and maintain the app and video delivery system.

We do not use this information for advertising or user profiling.

Server logs are kept only for as long as needed for security, debugging, and service operation.

## 6. Third-Party Links

The app may include a button that opens the Yango Play app or the Yango Play page on Google Play.

When you leave What to Watch and open another app or website, their own privacy policy applies.

## 7. Data Sharing

We do not sell personal data.

We do not share personal data with advertisers.

Limited technical data may be processed by hosting or infrastructure providers only when needed to operate and deliver the app.

## 8. Children’s Privacy

What to Watch is not designed to collect personal information from children.

The app does not require users to create an account or provide personal details.

## 9. Security

We use reasonable technical measures to protect the app and its video delivery systems. However, no digital service can guarantee complete security.

## 10. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted in the updated version of this policy.

